---
title: Alert
---

p.-text Alert messages provide contextual feedback for user actions.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | To render an alert, use the class <code>m-alert</code>.
  | A contextual class (e.g. <code>-warning</code>) is required to provide proper styling.

h4 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--1
    each type in ['success', 'danger', 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']
      .m-alert.-bubble.-m--2(class=`-${type}`)
        = `This is a ${type} alert`
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -success" role="alert">This is a success alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -danger" role="alert">This is a danger alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -warning" role="alert">This is a warning alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -info" role="alert">This is an info alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -light" role="alert">This is a light alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -bubble -dark" role="alert">This is a dark alert</div>

h4 Icons
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    each val, type in {success:'icon-circle-check', danger:'icon-circle-warning', warning:'icon-warning', info:'icon-circle-info', light:'icon-circle-info-outline', dark:'icon-circle-info'}
      .m-alert.-bubble.-m2(class=`-${type}`)
        if (type == 'success')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else if (type == 'danger')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else if (type == 'warning')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else if (type == 'info')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else if (type == 'light')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else if (type == 'dark')
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
        else
          i.a-icon(class =`${val}`)
        = `This is a ${type} alert`
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -bubble -info" role="alert">
       <i class="a-icon icon-circle-info -text--info"></i>
       This is a info alert
    </div>

h5 Icon Center
p.-text Use the class <code>-center</code> to center the icons.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-m2.-center(class=`-info`)
      i.a-icon(class ='icon-circle-info -textInfo')
      = `Info alert with centered icon`
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -bubble -center -info" role="alert">
      <i class="a-icon icon-circle-info -text--info"></i>
      Info alert with centered icon
    </div>

h4 Titled
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-titled.-danger.-m2
      i.a-icon.icon-warning.-text--danger
      .m-alert__content
        h5.a-h5 Danger
        | This is a danger alert
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -bubble -titled -danger">
      <i class="a-icon icon-warning -text--danger"></i>
      <div class="m-alert__content">
        <h5 class="a-h5">Danger</h5>
        This is a danger alert
      </div>
    </div>

h4 Dismissible
p.-text A button can be added to allow the user to dismiss the alert.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-warning.-m2
      i.a-icon.icon-warning.-text--warning
      | This is a warning alert
      button(class='a-btn -icon -close -small')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -bubble -warning">
      <i class="a-icon icon-warning -text--warning"></i>
      This is a warning alert<button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
      <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>

